  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "What are the factors that shape the identities of people and contribute to a diverse society?",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "What are the experiences and effects of living in a diverse society?",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "How can we respond to diversity in society?",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Factors-that-shape-the-identities-of-people-and-diversity",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Factors that shape the identities of people and diversity",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "doc:Exploring-CItizenship-and-Governance",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", you learned that your ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "doc:Exploring-CItizenship-and-Governance#Sense-of-Identity",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "refers both to how you perceive yourself and how others peceive you",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "There are several main identities that are the target of categorisation when it comes to diversity.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Race and ethnicity",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Religion",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Socio-economic status",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Nationality",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Race-and-Ethnicity",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Race and Ethnicity",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Even though race and ethnicity are used interchangeably, they are different.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Race: Biological classification of people, which includes their physical characteristics",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Definition",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Ethnicity: The culture of a group of people who share the same ancestry customs and traditions that distinguish",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "them from other groups in society",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Definition",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A single race may have multiple ethnicities.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In Singapore, racial categorisation follows the CMIO system, which stands for Chinese, Malay, Indian, Others (search as European,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Eurasian, other Asians)",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "There are two main ways that Singapore uses this categorisation to make decisions regarding policies related to to race and ethnicity.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Group-Representation-Constituency-GRC",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Group Representation Constituency (GRC)",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Established in 1988, it ensures that minority races in Singapore are represented in parliament. A group of members of parliament",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "represent the interest of residents in the constituency. At least one of them in the group must belong to the Malay or Indian",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "community or another minority racial community.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Ethnic-Integration-Policy-EIP",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Ethnic Integration Policy (EIP)",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "It was introduced in 1989 to promote interaction and harmony between different ethnic groups in Singapore. Its main aim is to prevent",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the rise of ethnic enclaves.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The EIP ensures that there is a mix of various ethnic groups in each HDB block, based on the ethnic make-up of Singapore. Since different",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "ethnic groups live in the same block, they have opportunities to interact with one another.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Issues",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Issues",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "CMIO Has some issues regarding how it tends to overlook mixed race families, because it only recognises a member of a mixed race family",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "as one of the races, which may be inaccurate.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Religion",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Religion",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Singapore is a multireligious society. Different religions have different beliefs, values, practices and ways of life, which shape their identities.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "These different identities contribute to the diversity in Singapore.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Race and religion are somewhat related. For example, 98.8% of Malays follow Islam. However, only slightly more than half of the Indian population",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "follows Hinduism, with the rest spread across different religions. For the Chinese, less than half of the population is Buddhist, with the rest of",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "them being assorted religions and a quarter having none. Conclusion, race is not always a strong indicator of a person‚Äôs religion, and vice versa.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Socio-Economic-Status",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Socio-Economic Status",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Defined by the wealth\/income of people in a society. Generally, there are less people of higher SES, and they tend to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "enjoy more power\/luxury than others. It can surface in education, occupation, income, house\/car ownership, etc.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The government balances SES in the following categories:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Students: Burseries, free school meals, school fees subsidy (make education accessible)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Adults: SkillsFuture (by providing sponsored educational resources\/training) (make job opportunities accessible)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Elderly: CPF benefits (make retirement accessible)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Nationality",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Nationality",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "People of the same nationality are generally citizens of the same country and usually live together in a particular geographical area.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "They may also share a common history and language.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Experiences-and-effects-of-living-in-a-diverse-society",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Experiences and effects of living in a diverse society",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Interactions in a diverse society and common space",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Experiences and effects of living in a diverse society",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Cultural exchange and appreciation",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Exchange of knowledge and skills",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Stereotypes, prejudice and discrimination",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Competition for resources",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Common space: A physical location and\/or a social space where different groups of people, interact,",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "cooperate, or collaborate with each other.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Definition",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Example of a common space is the void deck in public housing estates. They provide opportunities for residents to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "meet interact and bond.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "When living in a diverse Society, there are generally four things that happen.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Positive:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Cultural exchange and appreciation",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Exchange of knowledge and skills",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Negative:",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Stereotypes, prejudice and discrimination",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Competition for resources",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Interacting with people of different races as ethnicities, religions and social economic status allow for cultural",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "exchange take place. One outcome of cultural exchange is a deeper understanding and appreciation of customs and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "traditions of Singapore‚Äôs diverse ethnic groups. One example, result of this is fusion food, where different cuisines",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "are put together to create new ones.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A diverse society can also facilitate the exchange of knowledge and skills. Usually this comes in the form of foreign",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "investments and companies that come to Singapore and provide skills and training to local employees.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "However, in a diverse society like Singapore, there is the possibility of stereotypes, prejudice and discrimination.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Stereotype: Generalised association of certain characteristics or assumptions with a particular group of people",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Definition",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Prejudice: Attitudes or feelings towards other groups that are not based on reasons or fact. Stereotypes",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "and xenophobia are examples of prejudice.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Definition",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Discrimination: When a person acts on prejudiced beliefs by hurting or excluding a group",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Definition",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Finally, inflow of foreigners into Singapore means competition for jobs and infrastructure, such as housing and transport.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This competition, whether real or perceived, leads to tensions.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Responding-to-diversity-in-society",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Responding to diversity in society",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Citizens and government responding to socio-cultural diversity",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Responses of citizens as individuals and community groups",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Responses of government",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        },
                        {
                          "items" : [
                            {
                              "content" : [
                                {
                                  "inlineContent" : [
                                    {
                                      "text" : "Assimilationist policy and its tensions",
                                      "type" : "text"
                                    }
                                  ],
                                  "type" : "paragraph"
                                }
                              ]
                            },
                            {
                              "content" : [
                                {
                                  "inlineContent" : [
                                    {
                                      "text" : "Integration policy and its tensions",
                                      "type" : "text"
                                    }
                                  ],
                                  "type" : "paragraph"
                                }
                              ]
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "unorderedList"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Citizens and government responding to socio-economic diversity",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Responses of citizens as individuals and community groups",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Responses of government",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        },
                        {
                          "items" : [
                            {
                              "content" : [
                                {
                                  "inlineContent" : [
                                    {
                                      "text" : "A government-financed approach and its challenges",
                                      "type" : "text"
                                    }
                                  ],
                                  "type" : "paragraph"
                                }
                              ]
                            },
                            {
                              "content" : [
                                {
                                  "inlineContent" : [
                                    {
                                      "text" : "A shared responsibility approach and its challenges",
                                      "type" : "text"
                                    }
                                  ],
                                  "type" : "paragraph"
                                }
                              ]
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "unorderedList"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Social cohesion refers to close relationships between individuals and groups of people, and the feelings of solidarity",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "they have as one unit. These bonds can be weakened or broken when individuals are insensitive, hurtful, or disrespectful",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "with regard to diverse differences.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Assimilationsist-policies-in-France",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Assimilationsist policies in France",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In countries that adopt assimilationist policies, immigrants are expected to adopt the beliefs and practices of the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "majority group in the host country. Countries like Denmark, Germany and France adopt these.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "France believes that the ideal of harmony in society is achieved on every individual, put aside their connections to",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "race, ethnicity and religion. France acknowledges the existence of diversity, but believes that the French national",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "identity should be prioritised over all others.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example, in 2004, France introduced a ban of clearly visible religious attire and symbols in public schools.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Integration-policies-in-Singapore",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Integration policies in Singapore",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Singapore uses the integration approach, where minority and immigrants retain their unique identities, while forging",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "common ground with the majority group in the host country.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Managing-Issues-of-Socio-economic-Diversity",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Managing Issues of Socio-economic Diversity",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Sweden practices, a government finance approach to provide social services to their citizens, regardless of socio-economic",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "status. For example, healthcare services such as hospital care, medicine and dental care are publicly funded. Tuition",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "fees for tertiary education are also fully subsidised for Swedish students.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This heavily government financed approach is funded by imposing high taxes. However, with an ageing population, the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "demand for social services is increasing.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Singapore on the other hand, adopts a shared responsibility approach. Basically what that means is that the government",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "subsidise some stuff, but the individual does the rest.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For example, in the healthcare system, there are multiple tears of protection.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Government subsidies help reduce the cost to the patient",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "MediShield Life pays for large hospital bills and selected outpatient treatments",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "MediSave helps pay for your or your family‚Äôs medical expenses",
